==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English, derived from Old English ''[[braegen]]'' and ''[[bregen]]''.

===Noun===
'''brain''' (''plural'' '''brains''')

#<!--DefA-->That part of the [[central nervous system]] of an [[animal]] located in the [[skull]] which controls the actions of the animal.
#<!--DefB-->An [[intelligent]] person.
#:''He was a total brain.''
#<!--DefC-->A person who provides the intelligence required for something.
#:''the brain behind the scheme''
#<!--DefD-->(''in plural'' '''brains''') [[Intellect]].
#:''He has a lot of brains.''
#<!--DefE-->By analogy with a human brain, the part of a [[machine]] or [[computer]] that performs [[calculation]]s.
#:''The computer's brain is capable of millions of calculations a second.''

